verses.text_plain: And Jacob went on his way, and the angels of God met him.
verses.verse_html: 1And Jacob went on his way, and the angels of God met him.

verses.text_plain: And when Jacob saw them, he said, This is God’s host: and he called the name of that place Mahanaim.
verses.verse_html:
2And when Jacob saw them, he said, This is God’s host: and he called the name of that place Mahanaim. ▼
▼ Mahanaim: that is, Two hosts, or, camps

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Mahanaim: that is, Two hosts, or, camps
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Mahanaim: that is, Two hosts, or, camps

verses.text_plain: And Jacob sent messengers before him to Esau his brother unto the land of Seir, the country of Edom.
verses.verse_html:
3And Jacob sent messengers before him to Esau his brother unto the land of Seir, the country of Edom. ▼
▼ country: Heb. field

verses.text_plain: And he commanded them, saying, Thus shall ye speak unto my lord Esau; Thy servant Jacob saith thus, I have sojourned with Laban, and stayed there until now:
verses.verse_html: 4And he commanded them, saying, Thus shall ye speak unto my lord Esau; Thy servant Jacob saith thus, I have sojourned with Laban, and stayed there until now:

verses.text_plain: And I have oxen, and asses, flocks, and menservants, and womenservants: and I have sent to tell my lord, that I may find grace in thy sight.
verses.verse_html: 5And I have oxen, and asses, flocks, and menservants, and womenservants: and I have sent to tell my lord, that I may find grace in thy sight.

verses.text_plain: And the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, We came to thy brother Esau, and also he cometh to meet thee, and four hundred men with him.
verses.verse_html: 6And the messengers returned to Jacob, saying, We came to thy brother Esau, and also he cometh to meet thee, and four hundred men with him.

verses.text_plain: Then Jacob was greatly afraid and distressed: and he divided the people that was with him, and the flocks, and herds, and the camels, into two bands;
verses.verse_html: 7Then Jacob was greatly afraid and distressed: and he divided the people that was with him, and the flocks, and herds, and the camels, into two bands;

verses.text_plain: And said, If Esau come to the one company, and smite it, then the other company which is left shall escape.
verses.verse_html: 8And said, If Esau come to the one company, and smite it, then the other company which is left shall escape.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob said, O God of my father Abraham, and God of my father Isaac, the Lord which saidst unto me, Return unto thy country, and to thy kindred, and I will deal well with thee:
verses.verse_html: 9And Jacob said, O God of my father Abraham, and God of my father Isaac, the Lord which saidst unto me, Return unto thy country, and to thy kindred, and I will deal well with thee:

verses.text_plain: I am not worthy of the least of all the mercies, and of all the truth, which thou hast shewed unto thy servant; for with my staff I passed over this Jordan; and now I am become two bands.
verses.verse_html:
10I am not worthy of the least of all the mercies, and of all the truth, which thou hast shewed unto thy servant; for with my staff I passed over this Jordan; and now I am become two bands. ▼
▼ I am not…: Heb. I am less than all

tokens.text: I am not worthy of the least
and now I am become two

footnotes.body_text: ▼ I am not…: Heb. I am less than all
footnotes.body_html: ▼ I am not…: Heb. I am less than all

verses.text_plain: Deliver me, I pray thee, from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau: for I fear him, lest he will come and smite me, and the mother with the children.
verses.verse_html:
11Deliver me, I pray thee, from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau: for I fear him, lest he will come and smite me, and the mother with the children. ▼
▼ with: Heb. upon

tokens.text: I pray thee, from the hand

verses.text_plain: And thou saidst, I will surely do thee good, and make thy seed as the sand of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude.
verses.verse_html: 12And thou saidst, I will surely do thee good, and make thy seed as the sand of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude.

verses.text_plain: And he lodged there that same night; and took of that which came to his hand a present for Esau his brother;
verses.verse_html: 13And he lodged there that same night; and took of that which came to his hand a present for Esau his brother;

verses.text_plain: Two hundred she goats, and twenty he goats, two hundred ewes, and twenty rams,
verses.verse_html: 14Two hundred she goats, and twenty he goats, two hundred ewes, and twenty rams,

verses.text_plain: Thirty milch camels with their colts, forty kine, and ten bulls, twenty she asses, and ten foals.
verses.verse_html: 15Thirty milch camels with their colts, forty kine, and ten bulls, twenty she asses, and ten foals.

verses.text_plain: And he delivered them into the hand of his servants, every drove by themselves; and said unto his servants, Pass over before me, and put a space betwixt drove and drove.
verses.verse_html: 16And he delivered them into the hand of his servants, every drove by themselves; and said unto his servants, Pass over before me, and put a space betwixt drove and drove.

verses.text_plain: And he commanded the foremost, saying, When Esau my brother meeteth thee, and asketh thee, saying, Whose art thou? and whither goest thou? and whose are these before thee?
verses.verse_html: 17And he commanded the foremost, saying, When Esau my brother meeteth thee, and asketh thee, saying, Whose art thou? and whither goest thou? and whose are these before thee?

verses.text_plain: Then thou shalt say, They be thy servant Jacob’s; it is a present sent unto my lord Esau: and, behold, also he is behind us.
verses.verse_html: 18Then thou shalt say, They be thy servant Jacob’s; it is a present sent unto my lord Esau: and, behold, also he is behind us.

verses.text_plain: And so commanded he the second, and the third, and all that followed the droves, saying, On this manner shall ye speak unto Esau, when ye find him.
verses.verse_html: 19And so commanded he the second, and the third, and all that followed the droves, saying, On this manner shall ye speak unto Esau, when ye find him.

verses.text_plain: And say ye moreover, Behold, thy servant Jacob is behind us. For he said, I will appease him with the present that goeth before me, and afterward I will see his face; peradventure he will accept of me.
verses.verse_html:
20And say ye moreover, Behold, thy servant Jacob is behind us. For he said, I will appease him with the present that goeth before me, and afterward I will see his face; peradventure he will accept of me. ▼
▼ of me: Heb. my face

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of me: Heb. my face

verses.text_plain: So went the present over before him: and himself lodged that night in the company.
verses.verse_html: 21So went the present over before him: and himself lodged that night in the company.

verses.text_plain: And he rose up that night, and took his two wives, and his two womenservants, and his eleven sons, and passed over the ford Jabbok.
verses.verse_html: 22And he rose up that night, and took his two wives, and his two womenservants, and his eleven sons, and passed over the ford Jabbok.

verses.text_plain: And he took them, and sent them over the brook, and sent over that he had.
verses.verse_html:
23And he took them, and sent them over the brook, and sent over that he had. ▼
▼ sent them: Heb. caused to pass

footnotes.body_text: ▼ sent them: Heb. caused to pass
footnotes.body_html: ▼ sent them: Heb. caused to pass

verses.text_plain: And Jacob was left alone; and there wrestled a man with him until the breaking of the day.
verses.verse_html:
24And Jacob was left alone; and there wrestled a man with him until the breaking of the day. ▼
▼ breaking…: Heb. ascending of the morning

footnotes.body_text: ▼ breaking…: Heb. ascending of the morning
footnotes.body_html: ▼ breaking…: Heb. ascending of the morning

verses.text_plain: And when he saw that he prevailed not against him, he touched the hollow of his thigh; and the hollow of Jacob’s thigh was out of joint, as he wrestled with him.
verses.verse_html: 25And when he saw that he prevailed not against him, he touched the hollow of his thigh; and the hollow of Jacob’s thigh was out of joint, as he wrestled with him.

verses.text_plain: And he said, Let me go, for the day breaketh. And he said, I will not let thee go, except thou bless me.
verses.verse_html: 26And he said, Let me go, for the day breaketh. And he said, I will not let thee go, except thou bless me.

tokens.text: I will not let thee go

verses.text_plain: And he said unto him, What is thy name? And he said, Jacob.
verses.verse_html: 27And he said unto him, What is thy name? And he said, Jacob.

verses.text_plain: And he said, Thy name shall be called no more Jacob, but Israel: for as a prince hast thou power with God and with men, and hast prevailed.
verses.verse_html:
28And he said, Thy name shall be called no more Jacob, but Israel: for as a prince hast thou power with God and with men, and hast prevailed. ▼
▼ Israel: that is, A prince of God

tokens.text: for as a prince hast thou power

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Israel: that is, A prince of God
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Israel: that is, A prince of God

verses.text_plain: And Jacob asked him, and said, Tell me, I pray thee, thy name. And he said, Wherefore is it that thou dost ask after my name? And he blessed him there.
verses.verse_html: 29And Jacob asked him, and said, Tell me, I pray thee, thy name. And he said, Wherefore is it that thou dost ask after my name? And he blessed him there.

verses.text_plain: And Jacob called the name of the place Peniel: for I have seen God face to face, and my life is preserved.
verses.verse_html:
30And Jacob called the name of the place Peniel: for I have seen God face to face, and my life is preserved. ▼
▼ Peniel: that is, The face of God

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Peniel: that is, The face of God
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Peniel: that is, The face of God

verses.text_plain: And as he passed over Penuel the sun rose upon him, and he halted upon his thigh.
verses.verse_html: 31And as he passed over Penuel the sun rose upon him, and he halted upon his thigh.

verses.text_plain: Therefore the children of Israel eat not of the sinew which shrank, which is upon the hollow of the thigh, unto this day: because he touched the hollow of Jacob’s thigh in the sinew that shrank.
verses.verse_html: 32Therefore the children of Israel eat not of the sinew which shrank, which is upon the hollow of the thigh, unto this day: because he touched the hollow of Jacob’s thigh in the sinew that shrank.
